content:
As previously communicated, the contractual requirement to use multi-factor authentication (MFA) for Salesforce products is in full effect. Instead of technically enforcing MFA, a new notification model has been implemented. If a customer disables the MFA org-wide setting, admins receive periodic in-app warnings until MFA is re-enabled.

This change applies to Lightning Experience and all mobile app versions in all editions. MFA is now turned on by default for direct logins to existing production orgs and newly created ones.

The contractual requirement to use MFA remains in effect for direct and SSO logins to products built on the Salesforce Platform. If the Require multi-factor authentication setting is disabled, admins see a warning prompt advising that the org is out of compliance.

Admins can dismiss this prompt, but it reappears periodically until the MFA org-wide setting is turned back on.
title: Salesforce MFA Reminders for Admins
